# Sys Driver Rust

This library implements the fuchsia.gpu.magma FIDL interfaces for a GPU driver.
A driver wishing to use this library should implement the traits found in
`trait.rs`.

This library is based off of the C++ library.

## Threading Architecture

The CombinedDevice FIDL server will create a new thread whenver a client calls
connect.

The Context and Connection objects are not required to be
thread safe as they will only be accessed by the client thread.

The Device and Driver object are required to be thread safe as they can be
accessed by the Client threads.

The Buffer and Semaphore objects are required to be thread safe as they
will be passed to the device thread.

## Differences

Here are known differences between the two libraries:
- In rust the connection is created on the connection thread, where in C++ it is created
  on the device thread.
